* code:
- set_folder.R: Sets folders containing the code, the data, the Stan fit and the data where the generated plots and simulations are saved. ONLY THIS NEEDS TO BE MODIFIED when code is moved. FOLDER where the Stan model fit is saved NEEDS TO BE CREATED!
- grey_seal.stan: Stan file for population model

  RUNNING THE CODE
- fit_stan_model.R: START from this and continue in the below order. Reads in data and runs the Stan model, saves the fit. Runs very long.

- readin.R: reads in the Stan fit, extracts the samples, reads in the observed data. Set the folder where plots are saved.
- plotting_functions.R: helper function for plotting pretty plots
- forecast_function.R: has the simulate() function, which runs the simulation and the simulate_growth() function needed for comparison to Caroll
- simulation_setup.R: sets the scenarios for the simulation (harvest size, hunting selectivity (called bias in the code), herring quality) and for how many years to run the simulation
- simulation.R: runs the simulation, with the setup of the above. Takes LONG to run. saves in a csv file the median and 95%CI of simulated total population sizes & birth rates over the years + the whole sample for year 2080 + composition for (historical bias+historical herring quality+1311harvest) scenario. -> used then by analysis.Rmd for plotting

- analysis.Rmd: this produces all of the analysis/results of the manuscript (excluding appendix)

- detailed_hunting.R: distribution of hunting throughput the years -> Appendix:Hunting, to explain linearly decreasing hunting effort
- model_check.Rmd: Plots for posterior predictive checks

- data_processing: process raw data into processed data ready to read in by rest of the code
- caroll_comparison: all the code of Caroll's model and code for comparing the two models

* simulations: folder containing simulation results

* source_data: Data saved in .csv format, to be processed by "data_processing" files to create files in "processed_data"

* processed_data: Data processed, ready to be read in by the stan model fitting

* caroll_data: Caroll et al.'s data, needed for comparing their model to ours

Caroll et al. code and data acquired from https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10528563 and  https://github.com/DaireCarroll2023/Grey-Seal-PVA

